bid_attachment_description: RTTT Charter School Program Technical Assistant
short_description: RTTT Charter School Program Technical Assistant
description: To provide technical assistance to local education agencies and charter schools for Race to the Top initiatives.  Tasks include: facilitation of the implementation of the new Maryland Charter School Quality Standards with charter school stakeholders including charter school developers and operators, county liaisons; creating and administering surveys for school leadership team members on the new Maryland Charter School Quality Standards; and Self-Assessment Tool; development of Model Policy Resource Guide for charter schools in Maryland, and, providing technical assistance requested by LEAs and charter schools in identified capacities.  This support position is intended to help guide charter school stakeholders to implement best practices linked to the development of high performing charter schools and to highlight program accomplishments. Note:  Please refer to RFQ #R00R320050 when contacting Alan Delman.All communications pertaining to this RFQ shall be addressed to Alan Delman by e-mail only.

description: The Department of Health and Mental Hygiene, Office of Information Technology, Infrastructure and Network Division is soliciting bids to provide alarm monitoring services:?	The Department of Health and Mental Hygiene, Office of Information Technology,  requires third party alarm monitoring services for a 24-hour, 7-day per week data center located in Baltimore, Maryland.?	The Department requires third party monitoring of certain conditions inside the Data Center facility utilizing the alarm monitoring equipment installed at the Data Center.?	Conditions such as temperature, fire suppression system activation, monitoring electrical power, and water and/or flooding must be monitored on a 24-hour, 7-day per week, 365 day per year basis.

description: Human Services - The Maryland State Department of Human Resources (Department), Social Services Administration (SSA) intends to award multiple Contracts to Offerors to provide Residential Child Care (RCC) services in Maryland through 7 Program categories:  Developmentally Disabled Programs (DD); Diagnostic Evaluation and Treatment Programs (DETP); Group Home Programs (GHP); High Intensity Group Home Programs (HIGH) (includes Therapeutic Group Homes - TGH); High Intensity Group Home Programs for Teen Girls with Anti-social Behaviors (HIGH-TGASB); Medically Fragile Programs (MFP); and Psychiatric Respite Programs (PR).  RCC facilities will be located throughout the State and serve foster care children under the care of the Department (see Section 3.3).  Contracts resulting from this RFP shall be for a period of 3 years beginning on or about April 1, 2013 and ending on or about March 31, 2016, with two 1-year options to be renewed at the sole discretion of the State.

Test shall have a built-in internal IgG biological control, a minimum Sensitivity of 99.7% and Specificity of 99.9%, be approved for Whole Blood Calillary and Venipunture, Plasma and Serum Samples. description: Queen Anne?s County is soliciting proposals to manage, maintain and run the rental component and food concessions of Matapeake Clubhouse (201 Clubhouse Drive, Stevensville). The complexities of the property which include a public beach need to be taken into consideration when submitting a proposal. It should be noted that the beach is to remain open to the public.  Memorial Day to Labor Day the beach is open for swimming and rental of the facility shall not interfere with these operations. The maintenance of the beach will remain the responsibility of the county along with the bathroom trailer. Contractors should take into consideration maintenance of the grounds (excluding the beach and bathroom trailer) consisting of: general landscaping and cleaning the grounds surrounding the clubhouse area. The rental component of the Clubhouse is to closely mirror current time limitations of events during peak beach seasons (May 1 through September 30); during this time no event can begin
